      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so since polyester is \"man-made\" and engineered in a lab while silk is biological, does that mean the performance of synthetic fibers is always going to feel more \"souless\" or artificial compared to the natural stuff, or is that just a perception thing?",
